          "body": "The divine speech in v.10 ends not with a promise to the believer but with a declaration of God's own purpose: *I will be exalted among the nations, I will be exalted in the earth*. The verb (*rum*) is repeated for emphasis. The melting of nations and the breaking of weapons is not destruction for its own sake but the clearing of ground for God's exaltation. The psalm thus places the believer's trouble within the largest possible frame: every shaking of earth, every collapse of kingdom, every cessation of war serves the one end of God's universal exaltation. This is the same telos Paul names in Philippians 2:9-11 (every knee bowing, every tongue confessing) and Revelation 11:15 (the kingdom of the world becoming the kingdom of our Lord). The believer's refuge is not merely safe — it is on the winning side of history."
